      <h2>Getting started</h2>

      <h4>1. Install Atom</h4>
      <p>Download and install<a href="/">Atom</a>. It's free, open source, and cross-platform. You can use it on Windows, macOS, or Linux.</p>

      <h4>2. Install Teletype for Atom</h4>
      <p>Install the <a href="atom://settings-view/show-package?package=teletype">teletype</a>package to start collaborating today. If you need help, take a look at<a href="https://flight-manual.atom-editor.cc/using-atom/sections/atom-packages">how to install Atom packages</a>.</p>

      <hr>

      <h4>Share a portal</h4>
      <p>Click the <span class="octicon octicon-radio-tower" aria-label="Teletype"></span> icon in the Atom status bar, and flip the switch to start sharing a portal to your workspace. Then invite people to join your portal by sending them your portal URL.</p>

      <h4>Join a portal</h4>
      <p>Once someone has provided you with a link to their portal, simply follow the link to join the portal. The portal opens and all collaborators can edit together in real time.</p>
